## PURPOSE

This is the most cross-traditional event in the entire framework. Locate and transcribe the FLOOD/CATASTROPHE NARRATIVE from every tradition that has one, in original language + literal translation. Then pull every POST-FLOOD covenant/agreement/treaty text. Map both the convergences AND the divergences. The output is a SOURCE DOCUMENT and a COMPARISON TABLE.

**Claims to audit from the Narrative Skeleton:**
- The Engineer (Enki) warns the survivor through the wall — a technical exploit to circumvent a divine oath
- Multiple traditions describe the catastrophic agent as water + other elements (fire, ice, darkness)
- Survival via vessel (boat, underground vault, mountain refuge) with knowledge preservation protocols
- Post-flood reconciliation between Commander (Enlil) and Engineer (Enki) — no punishment recorded
- The post-flood treaty establishes: engineering constraints (death, population controls), dietary shift, territorial division (70 nations), the rebel's bounded license (proxy only, time-limited), and a 1000-year penalty clause for violation
- Different survivor groups inherit different versions of events — explaining why traditions diverge on details

