### 1. AKKADIAN — Atrahasis III and Gilgamesh XI

a) **Atrahasis Tablet III** (Lambert & Millard; or Lambert 2005 Babylonian Creation Myths) — THE PRIMARY FLOOD TEXT. Pull the FULL narrative:

- **The divine oath:** The gods agree — no warnings. What is the exact Akkadian? Who participates? Is Enki explicitly included in or excluded from the oath?

- **Enki's wall-speech:** The exact Akkadian of "Reed wall, reed wall! Wall, wall! Reed wall, hear! Wall, pay attention!" (*igāru igāru, kikkišu kikkišu! igāru šimi, kikkišu uṣur!* — verify transliteration). Then the instructions: build the boat, dimensions given. Pull EVERY dimension and specification.
  - CRITICAL: Does Enki address the wall or Atrahasis? The legal technicality — speaking to the wall, not the man — is the foundational "Enki move."

- **The boat construction:** Dimensions (exact numbers in the Akkadian — width, height, decking). How many decks? How sealed? What materials?

- **The loading:** What is taken aboard? Animals, family, craftsmen, "the seed of all living things" — exact Akkadian.

- **The storm:** Duration. Description. "The flood roared like a bull" — pull the imagery. The gods' reaction: "The gods were frightened by the flood, they retreated, they went up to the heaven of Anu, they crouched like dogs, they lay along the wall." This is NOT omnipotent gods — this is terrified beings fleeing their own weapon.

- **The aftermath:** The boat grounds. Atrahasis sends out birds (dove, swallow, raven). The offering: "The gods smelled the sweet savor, the gods gathered like flies over the offering."

- **Enlil's reaction:** "No life should have survived! No man should have lived through the destruction!" — exact Akkadian.

- **The reconciliation:** Enlil goes from rage to... what? Joint planning? Does the text explicitly describe a RECONCILIATION? Or simply a transition? Pull the exact passage.

- **The post-flood decrees:** New population controls — Enlil establishes death, infant mortality (pašittu-demon), celibate priestess classes (*nadītu*, *entu*). Pull the EXACT lines. These are the "engineering constraints" of the treaty.

b) **Gilgamesh XI** (George edition, if available in French/German commentary) — Utnapishtim's account.
- Pull the FULL flood narrative from Gilgamesh XI. Akkadian + translation.
- MAP every divergence from Atrahasis III. Where do they differ? Which details appear in one but not the other?
- The dimensions of the boat: Gilgamesh XI describes a CUBE (length = width = height = 120 cubits, 6 decks of 7 compartments each). Atrahasis has different proportions. Pull both sets of numbers.

### 2. HEBREW — Genesis 6-9

a) **Genesis 6:5-22, 7:1-24, 8:1-22, 9:1-17** — the COMPLETE flood narrative. Hebrew (Masoretic) + word-by-word.

Pull and map EVERY number:
- Dimensions of the ark (6:15): 300 cubits × 50 cubits × 30 cubits. Three decks.
- Duration: 40 days and 40 nights of rain (7:12). Waters prevail 150 days (7:24). 10th month, mountain tops visible (8:5). 40 more days, sends raven (8:6-7). Then dove three times (8:8-12).
- Noah's age markers: 600 years old at flood (7:6). 601 years, first month, first day — ground dry (8:13).

b) **Genesis 9:1-17 — The Noahide Covenant:**
- v.1-3: Dietary shift — "Every moving thing that lives shall be food for you, as I gave you the green plants, I now give you everything." Plants-only → meat now permitted.
- v.4: Blood restriction — "But you shall not eat flesh with its life, that is, its blood." The blood is RESERVED.
- v.5-6: Capital law — "Whoever sheds the blood of man, by man shall his blood be shed."
- v.8-17: The rainbow covenant — never again destruction by flood.
- Hebrew + word-by-word. Pull Rashi (Hebrew) and Ramban (Hebrew) on these verses.

c) **Deuteronomy 32:8 — The territorial division:**
- Masoretic: בְּהַנְחֵ֤ל עֶלְיוֹן֙ גּוֹיִ֔ם... יַצֵּ֖ב גְּבֻלֹ֣ת עַמִּ֑ים לְמִסְפַּ֖ר בְּנֵ֥י יִשְׂרָאֵֽל — "sons of Israel"
- Septuagint (LXX): ἀγγέλων θεοῦ — "angels of God"
- Dead Sea Scrolls (4QDeutj): בני אלהים — "sons of God/the gods"
- Pull ALL THREE versions side by side. The DSS reading is the oldest witness and says "sons of God/the gods" — 70 nations divided among 70 divine beings. The MT was CHANGED to "sons of Israel." This single verse is the load-bearing case for the 70-nations territorial division.

