## THE TREATY SYNTHESIS

After pulling all post-flood covenant/agreement texts, map the convergences:

1. **Engineering constraints:** Atrahasis III (death, infant mortality, celibate classes). Genesis 9 (lifespan cap implied). Any others?

2. **Dietary shift:** Genesis 9:3 (plants → now meat permitted). Blood reserved (9:4). Any parallel in other traditions?

3. **Territorial division:** Deut 32:8 (three versions — MT, LXX, DSS). 70 nations to 70 beings. Any parallel in other traditions' post-flood organization?

4. **The rebel's bounded license:** Jubilees 10 (10% operational freedom). Q 7:14-18 (time + proxy-only rules). Any parallel?

5. **The penalty clause:** Revelation 20 (1000-year binding). Zahhak binding under Damāvand (Persian). Is the 1000-year number present in more than two traditions?

6. **Counter-knowledge:** Jubilees 10 ("teach Noah all their medicines"). Genesis 9 (no medicines mentioned). The Vara's contents (seeds, best specimens, knowledge). What does each tradition say was given to the survivors to DEFEND themselves?

